Three people impersonating DCI detectives have been arrested. Hillary Kyengo, James Kagecha and David Maluki were arrested on Tuesday for lying to the CEO of the Teachers Service Commission and attempting to extort money for some 'purported investigations'. The three suspects will be charged with attempting to obtain money by false pretences. In October, a man conning unsuspecting Kenyans on false promises to secure them jobs in Qatar was also arrested. The number of Kenyans seeking employment in the Middle East particularly the United Arab Emirates, Saudi Arabia, Qatar, and Dubai has been on the rise over the years. Read:Â Conman arrested for duping unemployed youth with foreign jobs Click here for the latest political news